[
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(5) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "John truly baptized with water.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—See Note on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 3:11",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The words threw the disciples back upon their recollection of their first admission to the Kingdom. Some of them, at least, must have remembered also the teaching which had told them of the new birth of water and of the Spirit (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 3:3-5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). Now they were told that their spirits were to be as fully baptised, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "i.e., ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "plunged, into the power of the Divine Spirit, as their bodies had then been plunged in the waters of the Jordan. And this was to be “not many days hence.” The time was left undefined, as a discipline to their faith and patience. They were told that it would not be long, lest faith and patience should fail.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Henry's Concise Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "1:1-5 Our Lord told the disciples the work they were to do. The apostles met together at Jerusalem; Christ having ordered them not to depart thence, but to wait for the pouring out of the Holy Spirit. This would be a baptism by the Holy Ghost, giving them power to work miracles, and enlightening and sanctifying their souls. This confirms the Divine promise, and encourages us to depend upon it, that we have heard it from Christ; for in Him all the promises of God are yea and amen.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Barnes' Notes on the Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "For John truly baptized ... - These are the words of Jesus to his apostles, and he evidently has reference to what was said of John's baptism compared with his own in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 3:11",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 1:33",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". In those verses John is represented as baptizing with water, but the Messiah who was to come, as baptizing with the Holy Spirit and with fire. This promise was now about to be fulfilled in a remarkable manner. See ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Not many days hence - This was probably spoken not long before his ascension, and of course not many days before the day of Pentecost. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "Not many days hence - This was probably spoken not long before his ascension, and of course not many days before the day of Pentecost. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "5. ye shall be baptized with the Holy Ghost not many days hence—ten days hence, as appears from Le 23:15, 16; but it was expressed thus indefinitely to exercise their faith.",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Poole's Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "For John truly baptized with water, Matthew 3:11",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "For John truly baptized with water, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Matthew 3:11",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; water being of a purifying nature, plentiful, and easy to come by. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "But ye shall be baptized with the Holy Ghost; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " his gifts and graces, which were (as water on baptized persons) largely bestowed upon them on the day of Pentecost: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "1. That the apostles and all others might be assured of the doctrine of the Gospel. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "2. That they might be enabled to fulfil their ministry, and obey our Saviour’s commands left with them. Not many days hence; it was but ten days after his ascension; but our Saviour would not prefix a certain day, that they might watch every day. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "For John truly baptized with water,.... Or \"in water\", as he himself says, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 3:11",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " John's baptism was water baptism, an immersion of persons in water: he was the first administrator of it, and therefore is here mentioned by name; and his, and the baptism of the Spirit, are opposed; for there were others, as the disciples of Christ, that baptized in water as well as John: and these words are not to be understood of the words of the Lord, by the mouth of John, which the disciples heard, for they were not then called when John spoke the words in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 3:11",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " nor indeed are they the same with these; but these are the words of Christ himself, and which the apostles heard from his own mouth, as is clear from ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 11:16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " though they are not recorded by any of the evangelists; and these are not the only words which Luke repeats, that the evangelists are silent about; see ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 20:35",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "but ye shall be baptized with the Holy Ghost; that is, by himself; for it is Christ's prerogative to baptize with the Spirit, as John foretold of him, and it designs such an extraordinary and plentiful donation of the gifts of the Spirit, as may be expressed by a baptism; in which the apostles, on the day of \"Pentecost\", were, as it were, to be immersed, and with them covered; as Cyril of Jerusalem (h) observes, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "\"as he,    , \"who is plunged in water, and baptized\", is encompassed by the water on every side, so are they that are wholly baptized by the Spirit. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Not many days hence; within ten days, for this was on the fortieth day from his death, which was at the passover, these words were said; and on the fiftieth day from thence was the feast of Pentecost, when this had its fulfilment, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(h) Cateches. 17. sect. 8. p. 247. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "(h) Cateches. 17. sect. 8. p. 247. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Geneva Study Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cverse2",
        "text": "For John truly baptized with water; but ye shall be baptized {d} with the Holy Ghost not many days hence.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "For John truly baptized with water; but ye shall be baptized ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "cverse3",
            "text": "{d}",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " with the Holy Ghost not many days hence.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(d) Either by the Father, or by me: so that either the Father or Christ is set here contrasted with John, as the Holy Spirit is contrasted with water, as things that are comparable to one another.",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
